.:: Puzzle 2x6-Level-2-5::.
City: new-york, venice, san-francisco, marseilles, edinburgh, colone
The people grow 6 different varities of flowers: dahlia, begonia, bellflower, sunflower, tulip, balloon-flower
1. the person traveling to new-york is on the left of the person traveling to marseilles##1
2. the person traveling to san-francisco is on the right of the person who growsbellflower##1
3. the person who growsbegonia is on the right of the person who growssunflower##1
4. the person traveling to venice is between the person traveling to san-francisco and the person traveling to edinburgh##2
5. the person who growsbellflower is on the right of the person traveling to marseilles##1
6. the person who growsballoon-flower is on the left of the person who growssunflower##1
7. the person who growsdahlia is on the left of the person traveling to colone##1
8. the person traveling to edinburgh is on the far right##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |     2     |    3    |   4    |   5   |    6     |
| City   | new-york   | marseilles    | colone | san-francisco | venice | edinburgh   |
| Flower         | tulip | dahlia | bellflower | balloon-flower | sunflower  | begonia |

